                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d464">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hill</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Choate</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1901-05-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 22, 1901</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 636.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: With reference to the Department’s No. 482, of
                    November I last, you are instructed to report what action you have taken in the
                    matter of the request that Mr. William F. Smith, an American citizen, detained
                    on St. Helena as a prisoner of war, be released on parole.</p>
                <p>In consequence of a letter from the Hon. Frank E. Wilson, M. C., of the 16th
                    instant, you are instructed to recall the matter to the attention of the British
                    Government.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">David J. Hill</hi>,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
